    {
      "id": "91d344f88474b9af39b4a009393e4c2fbdf97cd9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-11-24 16:55:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWhile this fixes the immediate problem, it does not fix similar problems in the future. It would be better if the DKMS.conf file was automatically regenerated at build time so that it included the actual list of modules to be built. Otherwise, since we do not build DKMS RPMs for every patch I suspect that you will have an ongoing series of problems building DKMS as modules are added and removed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "6c37738cb6e516068ff5aed19af2134d968fa74e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 229,
        "name": "Bruno Faccini",
        "email": "bfaccini@nvidia.com",
        "username": "bfaccini"
      },
      "date": "2014-12-02 18:45:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAndreas, sure we know from the beginning that to rely on a static list of modules is a big limitation. But, OTOH to have it created dynamically is a big issue. Where/how can we get/build the exact list of modules from the Lustre source tree and at the time where dkms.conf is created ?? Can we rely on the sub-dirs names ? Are there any systematic rule/macro/statement that we can rely on to browse Makefiles ??",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "bbb4dd399cb6002b213e0b90e40f5076d5634c58",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2015-01-20 22:18:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2\n\nI'm fine to land this patch for 2.7.0 since time is getting short.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
